\begin_layout Section
Description
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Historically,
 FM radio provided a dominating medium to organically explore music,
 curated by the on-air disc jockey.
 Radio has not enjoyed the popularity it has in the past,
 with many music listeners opting for streaming services for their discovery.
 What if we could have the best of both worlds?
 Introducing our FM Radio Explorer,
 we devise an embedded system that provides radio tuning capabilities,
 in addition to providing exploratory information on the current track,
 all from the same interface.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
At a high level,
 we will use LastFM's public-facing API to query the song & artist name from the FM playback (using the CC3200's WiFi Card).
 LastFM offers a wide variety of metadata and points of musical exploration,
 which will be discussed with higher granularity in Section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sec:Implementation"
plural "false"
